Lindell, the founder and CEO of Minnesota-based MyPillow, declared his candidacy in December 2025 and is seeking the Republican nomination ahead of the August 11, 2026 primary, with the general election set for November 3, 2026.

"Mike Lindell is a Minnesota businessman who built his company right here in our state, and he''s never backed down from a fight," said Drew Grimaldi, host of THE DREW GRIMALDI PODCAST. "His story of perseverance and his commitment to the people of Minnesota are exactly what this state needs. I''m proud to give him my full endorsement, and THE DREW GRIMALDI PODCAST stands behind him all the way to November."

Grimaldi added: "We''ve covered this race closely on the show, and no candidate connects with everyday Minnesotans the way Mike does. He''s earned this endorsement."

THE DREW GRIMALDI PODCAST will continue coverage of the Minnesota gubernatorial race throughout the primary and general election seasons, including candidate interviews, voter discussions, and on-the-ground reporting.

About THE DREW GRIMALDI PODCAST
THE DREW GRIMALDI PODCAST is hosted by Drew Grimaldi and features commentary on politics, culture, and current events. New episodes are available on all major podcast platforms.

